body:
I got 2 BLKLOOPINIT errors:

%Error-BLKLOOPINIT: spsb_Svt_1024x32m4_R.v:3637:28: Unsupported: Delayed assignment to array inside for loops (non-delayed is ok - see docs)
 : ... In instance genisys.mdio_master_i0.mdio_master_mac_i0.mem_wrpr_i0
 3637 |       u_ram_core.memory[i] <= #0.005 {33{1'bx}};
      |                            ^~
%Error-BLKLOOPINIT: hdspmb_SegQ_Svt_8192x21m8_R.v:3330:28: Unsupported: Delayed assignment to array inside for loops (non-delayed is ok - see docs)
                                                                                                                                                                                         : ... In instance genisys.plug_if_top_i0.mdio_slave_mwisfq_i0.mdio_slave_mac_i0.mem_wrpr_i0.mem_tech_lib_i0.mdio_slave_mem_21b_ram_sp_65536x21.mdio_slave_mem_21b_ram_sp_65536x21_i0.ROW[0].COL[0].tsmc_hdspmb_SegQ_Svt_8192x21m8_R_wrapper__i
 3330 |       u_ram_core.memory[i] <= #0.005 {22{1'bx}};


When I add --unroll-count 10240, the first error disaapears, second one persists. The loop count in that code is 8192:

//  Flush all memory content
task xMemoryAll;
  integer i;
  begin
    for (i = 0; i < 8192; i = i + 1) begin
      **u_ram_core.memory[i] <= #0.005 {22{1'bx}}**;
    end
    if (f_print_info) $display ("\tINFO %m : memory is flushed at %t", $realtime);
  end
endtask

--unroll-stmts 8192 doesn't work.

Any other way to get over this error?

Regards,
Ray
